Response 2:
Pre-Meeting Notes: Fetch N Flavour’s Packaging Requirements

Introduction to Fetch N Flavour:
We are a company specializing in branded dog snacks and small meals for hospitality businesses. Our product line includes personalized treats and meals for dog-friendly hotels, restaurants, and other establishments. We focus on creating customized, eco-friendly packaging that reflects the branding of each of our clients while maintaining high standards of sustainability and quality.

Current Packaging Challenges:

	•	Our initial packaging idea involved kraft boxes (dimensions: 65mm x 30mm x 140mm) with a window to display the product inside. However, we have encountered difficulties in integrating a moisture and fat barrier into the box, as our products have a high fat content, which could affect the integrity of the box.
	•	Maintaining product freshness and visibility is a priority, while ensuring the packaging meets environmental standards is equally important to us.

New Packaging Goals – Transition to Pouches:
We are now exploring the potential of compostable or recyclable pouches for our products, and we are looking for solutions that address the following key requirements:

	1.	Material & Structure:
	•	We are considering 50g-70g of product per pouch.
	•	The material should be biodegradable or compostable, with strong resistance to moisture and fat to preserve product quality.
	•	Ideally, the pouch should offer a clear window to allow customers to see the product inside, while ensuring that it doesn’t compromise the barrier properties of the packaging.
	2.	Sealing Mechanisms:
	•	We want the pouches to have resealable features (such as zippers) to ensure product freshness after opening.
	•	Tamper-evident seals are also preferred to ensure product integrity.
	3.	Sustainability & Branding:
	•	Sustainability is at the core of our packaging strategy. We’re looking for pouches that are fully compostable or recyclable, ideally made from FSC-certified or similar eco-friendly materials.
	•	The packaging should allow for full-color branding using non-toxic, biodegradable inks. Our branding is an essential part of the customer experience, so we need the ability to incorporate client logos and colors effectively.
	•	We’re also interested in minimalist but eye-catching designs that complement the eco-friendly look of the pouch.
	4.	Samples and Costing:
	•	We would appreciate it if you could provide samples of small compostable pouches you have previously manufactured, especially those suited for dog food.
	•	We are looking for an understanding of pricing for small to medium-sized orders (starting around 50-100 units initially, scaling up as demand increases).
	•	If there are lead times for production, please share details so we can plan accordingly.
	5.	Additional Considerations:
	•	We’re open to discussing other innovative packaging solutions that may better suit our needs.
	•	If you have insights into how we can improve product shelf life while maintaining eco-friendly packaging, we’d be interested in hearing your recommendations.

Our Objective for the Meeting:
To explore the feasibility of using your compostable small pouches for our branded dog treats, and to understand what customization options, material choices, and cost structures are available. We are looking for long-term partners who can provide a sustainable packaging solution aligned with our vision of high-quality, eco-friendly, and branded dog products.

Thanks,
Edward
